    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="403"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 437.00/24.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 86.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d403fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1911#pg_126">For. Rel. 1911, p. 126</ref>.</note> in regard
                    to the so-called Cuban “insurrectionary claims,” I have the honor to report <pb
                        facs="0393" n="277" xml:id="pg_277"/> that the question is apparently
                    receiving serious attention from the Cuban Government.</p>
                <p>I understand that in the course of a day or two President Gómez is to begin a
                    series of conferences with members of the various interested committees of the
                    Cuban Congress, with his Cabinet, and with leaders of different political
                    parties and factions. * * *</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. M. Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
